rk Management Research Group" href="nmrg">NMRG</a></li> <li><a title="Routing Research Group" href="rrg">RRG</a></li> <li><a title="Scalable Adaptive Multicast Research Group" href="samrg">SAMRG</a></li> <li><a title="Software-Defined Networking Research Group" href="sdnrg">SDNRG</a></li> </ul> <h2>Other Activities</h2> <ul> <li> <a href='anrp'>Applied Networking Research Prize</a> </li> </ul> <h2>Internet Research Steering Group</h2> <ul> <li> <a href='chair'>IRTF Chair</a> </li> </ul> <ul> <li> <a href='irsg'>IRSG Members</a> </li> </ul> <h2>IPR</h2> <ul> <li> <a href='ipr'>Intellectual Property Rights</a> </li> </ul> <h2>Sponsors</h2> <ul> <li> <a href='http://ietf.org/'> <img alt='Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF)' height='53' src='img/ietf.png' width='100'> </a> </li> <li> <a href='http://isoc.org/'> <img alt='Internet Society (ISOC)' height='40' src='img/isoc.png' width='100'> </a> </li> </ul> </div> <div class='main'> <a id='content'></a> <div class='rightbar'> <h2>Chairs</h2> <p> The CFRG is chaired by <a href="http://mindspring.com/~dmcgrew/dam.htm">David McGrew</a> (<a href="mailto:mcgrew@cisco.com">mcgrew@cisco.com</a>) and Kevin Igoe (<a href="mailto:kmigoe@nsa.gov">kmigoe@nsa.gov</a>). </p> <h2>Mailing List</h2> <p> The CFRG mailing list is <a href="mailto:cfrg@irtf.org">cfrg@irtf.org</a>. To subscribe or access the list archives, visit the <a href="/mailman/listinfo/cfrg">mailman page</a>. </p> </div> <h2>Charter</h2> <p> The <span class='term'>Crypto Forum Research Group</span> (<a href="/cfrg">CFRG</a>) is a general forum for discussing and reviewing uses of cryptographic mechanisms, both for network security in general and for the <a href="http://ietf.org/">IETF</a> in particular. </p> <p>The <a href="/cfrg">CFRG</a> serves as a bridge between theory and practice, bringing new cryptographic techniques to the Internet community and promoting an understanding of the use and applicability of these mechanisms via Informational RFCs (in the tradition of, e.g., <a href="http://wiki.tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1321">RFC 1321</a> (MD5) and <a href="http://wiki.tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2104">RFC 2104</a> (HMAC). Our goal is to provide a forum for discussing and analyzing general cryptographic aspects of security protocols, and to offer guidance on the use of emerging mechanisms and new uses of existing mechanisms. <a href="http://ietf.org/">IETF</a> working groups developing protocols that include cryptographic elements are welcome to bring questions concerning the protocols to the <a href="/cfrg">CFRG</a> for advice.</p> <h2>Meetings and Membership</h2> The <a href="/cfrg">CFRG</a> meetings, membership, and mailing list are open to all who wish to participate. </div> </div> <div class='layout_footer'></div> </div> <div class='footer noprint'> <div class='left'> <div class='socialshareprivacy'></div> </div> <div class='right'> <span id='ipv6'></span> <span> <a href='http://validator.w3.org/check/referer'>HTML</a> </span> <span> <a href='http://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/check/referer'>CSS</a> </span> <span> Modified: <time datetime='2011-07-25'>2011-07-25</time> </span> </div> </div> <script src='//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.1/jquery.min.js'></script> <script>window.jQuery||document.write('<script src="jquery-1.7.1.min.js"><\/script>');$.getJSON("ipv6.json",function(b){if(b.ipv6){$("#ipv6").append("Thank you for using IPv6.")}});</script> <script src='socialshareprivacy.js'></script> <script>jQuery(document).ready(function(b){if(b(".socialshareprivacy").length>0){b(".socialshareprivacy").socialSharePrivacy({services:{facebook:{app_id:"194983820572921",dummy_img:"socialshareprivacy/images/dummy_facebook_en.png",txt_info:"Two clicks for more online privacy: Click here to enable the Facebook button. Enabling the button alone already transmits personal information to third parties.",txt_fb_off:"Facebook link active",txt_fb_on:"Facebook link inactive",language:"en_US",action:"recommend"},twitter:{dummy_img:"soc